  "name": "Building Blocks - BioClima OGC Building Blocks",
  "abstract": "Interactive BioClima viewer: https://maytetoscano.github.io/bblocks-bioclima/viewer/\n\nRegister of OGC Building Blocks for Essential Biodiversity Variables (EBVs),\nderived indicators, bioclimatic zonification, data provenance and policy\nalignment with the Kunming-Montreal GBF. The pilot dataset is the Start of\nVegetation Active Period in Finland (2001-2018).\n",
  "description": "**Interactive map viewer:** https://maytetoscano.github.io/bblocks-bioclima/viewer/\n\n**Classified registry by family:** https://maytetoscano.github.io/bblocks-bioclima/viewer/registry.html\n\n**OGC Building Blocks viewer:** https://maytetoscano.github.io/bblocks-bioclima/bblocks/\n\nThis register defines BioClima-specific building blocks on top of the\nOGC CoverageJSON community standard. It includes:\n\n- A profile of CoverageJSON for BioClima EBV datasets.\n- Generic schemas for EBV records and indicator records.\n- Concrete EBV datasets for Finnish coniferous and deciduous vegetation.\n- The Phenological Change Indicator (PCI) and its bioclimatic zonification,\n  each with a Python implementation that the CI can re-run automatically.\n- A multilingual SKOS/RDF ontology building block used by EBVs, indicators,\n  policy alignment, provenance and zonification records.\n- W3C PROV-O provenance schemas for both EBVs and indicators.\n- Policy alignment schemas linking indicators to Kunming-Montreal GBF\n  targets and SDG 15.\n",
  "modified": "2026-05-18T07:32:44.776893",
  "tooling": {
    "bblocks-postprocess": {
      "commitId": "\"6b01f188cc614cc2e65f4bf86a2623f98f101dfd",
      "shortCommitId": "\"6b01f1",
      "date": "2026-05-12T22:31:51+00:00\""
    }
  },
